    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="529"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7757</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-07T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 8, 12.45 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>National Assembly to-day unanimously passed resolution ratifying all steps of
                    belligerency heretofore taken and began favorable consideration of a bill
                    amplifying the powers given Panaman President by law, which is fourth enclosure
                    to my despatch 1271, February 27, last,<note n="1" xml:id="d529fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> including the control of exports among others, and the
                    issuance of $500,000 of bonds additional to the former authorization if need
                    be.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
